Eurasia Drilling, Uralkali, Sberbank: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-05-17T20:02:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-17/eurasia-drilling-uralkali-sberbank-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in Russian trading in Moscow. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are from the previous close of trading.  Russia ’s 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell 0.9 percent to 1,608.66
yesterday. The dollar-denominated RTS Index dropped 0.9 percent
to 1,828.89.  Eurasia Drilling Co. (EDCL LI): The oilfield services
company is expected to issue an update on first quarter revenue.
The company added 0.8 percent to $30.15 in  London .  OAO  Uralkali (URKA)  : Uralkali’s board is set to make a
decision on dividends. The Russia’s largest potash producer by
market value fell 2 percent to $38 in London.  OAO Sberbank (SBER03 RX): The deputy chairman of Russia’s
biggest lender, Stanislav Kuznetsov, will speak on the bank’s
strategic and priority projects at a briefing in Moscow,
according to an e-mailed statement. The shares declined 1.7
percent to 96.38 rubles.  OAO Gazprom (GAZP RX): Russia’s  Finance Ministry  is
proposing a higher gas extraction tax for companies that own gas
pipelines than those that don’t have access, Interfax said,
citing Deputy Minister Sergei Shatalov. Gazprom, Russia’s
natural gas export monopoly, added 0.2 percent to 198.91 rubles.
OAO Novatek, Russia’s biggest independent gas producer, dropped
1.9 percent to 339.05 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow 
